VI'm here today to show my photographs of the Lakota.
p4
aVMany of you may have heard of the Lakota,
p5
aVor at least the larger group of tribes,
p6
aVcalled the Sioux.
p7
aVThe Lakota are one of many tribes that were moved off their land
p8
aVto prisoner-of-war camps,
p9
aVnow called reservations.
p10
aVThe Pine Ridge Reservation,
p11
aVthe subject of today's slide show,
p12
aVis located about 75 miles southeast of the Black Hills in South Dakota.
p13
aVIt is sometimes referred to as Prisoner of War Camp Number 334,
p14
aVand it is where the Lakota now live.
p15
aVNow, if any of you have ever heard of AIM,
p16
aVthe American Indian Movement,
p17
aVor of Russell Means,
p18
aVor Leonard Peltier,
p19
aVor of the standoff at Oglala,
p20
aVthen you know Pine Ridge is ground zero for Native issues in the US.
p21
aa(lp22
VSo I've been asked to talk a little bit today
p23
aVabout my relationship with the Lakota,
p24
aVand that's a very difficult one for me,
p25
aVbecause, if you haven't noticed from my skin color,
p26
aVI'm white,
p27
aVand that is a huge barrier on a Native reservation.
p28
aVYou'll see a lot of people in my photographs today.
p29
aVI've become very close with them, and they've welcomed me like family.
p30
aVThey've called me "brother" and "uncle,"
p31
aVand invited me again and again over five years.
p32
aVBut on Pine Ridge,
p33
aVI will always be what is called "wasichu."
p34
aV"Wasichu" is a Lakota word
p35
aVthat means "non-Indian,"
p36
aVbut another version of this word
p37
aVmeans "the one who takes the best meat for himself."
p38
aVAnd that's what I want to focus on \u2014
p39
aVthe one who takes the best part of the meat.
p40
aVIt means "greedy."
p41
aa(lp42
VSo take a look around this auditorium today.
p43
aVWe are at a private school in the American West,
p44
aVsitting in red velvet chairs
p45
aVwith money in our pockets.
p46
aVAnd if we look at our lives,
p47
aVwe have indeed taken the best part of the meat.
p48
aVSo let's look today at a set of photographs
p49
aVof a people who lost
p50
aVso that we could gain,
