aa(lp313
VThe suffering of indigenous peoples is not a simple issue to fix.
p314
aVIt's not something everyone can get behind
p315
aVthe way they get behind helping Haiti,
p316
aVor ending AIDS, or fighting a famine.
p317
aVThe "fix," as it's called,
p318
aVmay be much more difficult for the dominant society
p319
aVthan, say, a $50 check
p320
aVor a church trip to paint some graffiti-covered houses,
p321
aVor a suburban family
p322
aVdonating a box of clothes they don't even want anymore.
p323
aVSo where does that leave us?
p324
aVShrugging our shoulders in the dark?
